               -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------                         


    Iterable Interface:
    ---------------------
     -> It is root for entire collection heirarchy 
     -> If a class implements iterable then it can be traversed.
     -> For the entire structure the uniform step of traversing is defined in Iterable.

     Iterable<String> fruits = Arrays.asliist("Kiwi", "Mango", "Apple");
     for(String str: fruits){
        sout(str);
     }
   
    Collection Interface:
    --------------------
    -> It extends Iterable interface.
    -> In iterable you will have only declaration about traversing, but where in Collection it declares how you store, manipulate and manage data.

Store:
    Add/Remove - add(e)
Manipilate
    Reomve -  remove(e)
    set element in position - set(index, element)    
    BulkOperation - addAll(), removeAll();
  Manage  
    Conversion - toArray() 
    Qerying      - Size(), isEmpty()